New England Revolution have confirmed that their player, Matt Turner has signed for Arsenal. New England Revolution disclosed this in a statement via their website on Friday. Recall that Arsenal have been heavily linked with Turner in January and the MLS side have now confirmed the American will make the move to the Premier League side in the summer. “The New England Revolution have agreed to terms for goalkeeper Matt Turner to join Arsenal of the English Premier League in a summer transfer for an undisclosed fee pending completion of a medical,” the statement read in part. “Turner, the 2021 Allstate MLS Goalkeeper of the Year, is expected to join Arsenal in late June 2022,” it added. Arsenal had agreed on a £5.8 million deal that would include an additional £2m in add-ons for Turner.